WEBVTT

00:07.090 --> 00:10.844
[hairdresser] There.
We can adjust the length
further if you want.

00:10.844 --> 00:12.554
No, it's perfect!

00:12.554 --> 00:15.098
[gasps] Oh, how about adding
a pink headscarf?

00:15.098 --> 00:17.226
-What do you think?
-You're already so beautiful.

00:17.226 --> 00:20.646
I'm not sure my heart
could handle the scarf.
[chuckles]

00:20.646 --> 00:24.107
Thank you for always
being there for me, Jule.

00:24.107 --> 00:26.818
You're gonna need new threads
to go with the hair.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.363
[Rose sighs]

00:29.363 --> 00:32.532
[Marinette]
<i> In the daytime, I'm Marinette.</i>

00:32.532 --> 00:35.577
<i> Just a normal girl
with a normal life.</i>

00:35.577 --> 00:38.914
<i> But there's something about me
that no one knows yet.</i>

00:38.914 --> 00:40.707
<i> Because I've got a secret.</i>

00:40.707 --> 00:41.667
[theme song playing]

00:41.667 --> 00:43.377
♪<i> Miraculous,
simply the best!</i> ♪

00:43.377 --> 00:46.421
♪<i> Up to the test
when things go wrong</i> ♪

00:46.421 --> 00:49.258
♪<i> Miraculous, the luckiest</i> ♪

00:49.258 --> 00:52.135
♪<i> The power of love
always so strong</i> ♪

00:52.135 --> 00:55.639
♪<i> Miraculous</i> ♪

00:55.639 --> 00:57.057
♪<i> Miraculous!</i> ♪

01:00.602 --> 01:01.812
[doorbell rings]

01:09.069 --> 01:12.114
-It's way too early--
-Special delivery
from the Dupain-Cheng Bakery!

01:12.114 --> 01:14.533
I felt like doing
something special with Adrien
this morning

01:14.533 --> 01:15.993
like having
breakfast together,

01:15.993 --> 01:17.411
but in a unique way.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.329
[Nathalie] You mean
unique like yesterday

01:19.329 --> 01:20.539
and the day before and...

01:20.539 --> 01:22.582
[laughs] No. It's not
the same thing at all.

01:22.582 --> 01:25.127
Yesterday we had croissants,
the day before was
pain au chocolat

01:25.127 --> 01:26.670
but today,
I brought chouquettes.

01:26.670 --> 01:28.755
Not to mention
the orange juice
is already pressed

01:28.755 --> 01:30.507
and the eggs
are already scrambled and...

01:30.507 --> 01:32.467
And the alarm clock
hasn't gone off yet.

01:32.467 --> 01:35.095
-[Marinette]
I've missed you so much!
-I've missed you too.

01:35.095 --> 01:36.638
You saw each other
at school yesterday.

01:36.638 --> 01:39.266
Actually, we saw each other
half an hour ago too

01:39.266 --> 01:40.559
on our good morning
video call.

01:40.559 --> 01:42.686
Technically, it was 28 minutes
and 12 seconds ago,

01:42.686 --> 01:45.856
-one of the longest waits
of my life!
-[Adrien chuckles]

01:47.357 --> 01:48.650
[Adrien] A letter?

01:48.650 --> 01:49.693
For me?

01:51.611 --> 01:54.489
Two movie tickets
for a 50th anniversary
screening

01:54.489 --> 01:56.908
of<i> Vampire Horrific
Musical Show?</i>

01:56.908 --> 01:59.828
-It was mailed from Roubaix!
-Your grandparents?

01:59.828 --> 02:01.872
<i> Surprise!</i>

02:01.872 --> 02:04.207
<i> Told you he'd
figure it out on his own.</i>

02:04.207 --> 02:05.584
<i> The kid's a genius!</i>

02:05.584 --> 02:07.461
<i> It'll be the only screening
in the world</i>

02:07.461 --> 02:09.629
<i> for the 50th anniversary
of the release</i>

02:09.629 --> 02:11.423
<i> of</i> Vampire Musical
Horrific Show.

02:11.423 --> 02:13.800
[Gabrielle]<i> The film
has gained a large
cult following</i>

02:13.800 --> 02:16.303
<i> 'cause the audience
participates during
the screening.</i>

02:16.303 --> 02:19.973
[Johnny]<i> You've got
squirt guns to make it rain
when it's raining in the film!</i>

02:19.973 --> 02:22.976
[Gabrielle]<i> You throw
paper planes around
when bats are flying!</i>

02:22.976 --> 02:24.478
You kiss when the two heroes

02:24.478 --> 02:26.313
declare their love
to each other.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.482
That's how we shared
our first kiss.

02:28.482 --> 02:30.984
-Those are
lovely fangs you got!
-Mmm.

02:30.984 --> 02:33.695
-Oh, bite me tender!
-[growls]

02:33.695 --> 02:35.781
We're going to Paris
for the occasion

02:35.781 --> 02:38.241
and we thought
you two lovebirds
could join us.

02:38.241 --> 02:40.160
Like family bonding, you know?

02:40.160 --> 02:42.162
Wait, it's a horror movie?

02:42.162 --> 02:43.663
[Johnny laughing]<i> Oui!</i>

02:43.663 --> 02:46.166
<i> But with songs!
Amazing, no?</i>

02:46.166 --> 02:47.751
You'll need costumes.
You don't go see

02:47.751 --> 02:49.461
the<i> Vampire Horrific
Musical Show</i>

02:49.461 --> 02:50.879
without dressing up
like a vampire.

02:50.879 --> 02:53.423
-It's tradition.
-You know the movie, Nathalie?

02:56.259 --> 02:57.344
I've heard of it.

02:57.344 --> 02:59.012
Well, thank you,
Grandma, Grandpa,

02:59.012 --> 03:01.681
but Marinette doesn't
really enjoy horror movies.

03:01.681 --> 03:04.601
What? Nuh-uh! Old Marinette
didn't like those movies,

03:04.601 --> 03:06.978
but new Marinette,
AKA Adrien's girlfriend

03:06.978 --> 03:10.232
is not afraid of anything,
especially horror movies!

03:10.232 --> 03:12.025
-[laughs]
-[Johnny]<i> Magnifique!</i>

03:12.025 --> 03:14.319
<i> We'll pick you up at 6:00 p.m.</i>

03:15.445 --> 03:17.614
Do you really like
horror movies now?

03:17.614 --> 03:19.408
[high-pitched]
Love 'em! Don't you?

03:19.408 --> 03:21.785
-You said that?
-I did!

03:21.785 --> 03:22.828
And what did he say?

03:22.828 --> 03:24.704
I don't know, Marinette.
I've never even

03:24.704 --> 03:27.082
watched a horror movie,
but it sounds like fun.

03:27.082 --> 03:28.417
I'm curious
to find out with you.

03:28.417 --> 03:30.919
And now I'm done for!

03:30.919 --> 03:34.631
That's right, you have
to go see the movie
with Adrien

03:34.631 --> 03:36.883
or you can kiss
your relationship goodbye!

03:36.883 --> 03:38.427
See? I told you!

03:38.427 --> 03:40.387
Stop talking nonsense, Trixx.

03:40.387 --> 03:42.139
Listen, girl,
you definitely do not have

03:42.139 --> 03:44.683
to go see this horror flick
if you're not
feeling up to it.

03:44.683 --> 03:47.644
But... [shudders]
What if Adrien likes the film?

03:47.644 --> 03:49.521
He'll think that we don't
have the same taste,

03:49.521 --> 03:50.981
that like the same things,

03:50.981 --> 03:52.607
and he won't love me anymore!

03:52.607 --> 03:55.318
Marinette, couples don't have
to do everything together

03:55.318 --> 03:56.528
or like the same exact things.

03:56.528 --> 03:59.281
-Do you and Nino
like the same things?
-Yeah.

03:59.281 --> 04:01.700
And do you always do
everything together?

04:01.700 --> 04:02.993
-Yep.
-See?

04:02.993 --> 04:05.036
Nino and I are Nino and I.

04:05.036 --> 04:07.414
Adrien and you
are Adrien and you.

04:07.414 --> 04:10.417
If horror movies aren't
your thing, just tell him.

04:11.126 --> 04:12.752
[sighs] You're right.

04:12.752 --> 04:15.422
Adrien and I are going
to the<i> Vampire Musical
Horrific Show</i> tonight

04:15.422 --> 04:17.299
and it's gonna be amazing!

04:18.133 --> 04:19.759
-[sighs]
-Oh, you're so lucky!

04:19.759 --> 04:22.137
I wanted to take Juleka
to see it for the first time,

04:22.137 --> 04:25.056
but the tickets sold out
a minute after they went
on sale.

04:25.056 --> 04:26.516
What a shame.

04:26.516 --> 04:30.103
If only there was someone
who had tickets
but didn't want to go see it.

04:30.103 --> 04:33.440
I don't know anyone quite
like that. Do you, Marinette?

04:33.440 --> 04:36.485
Nope. [chuckles awkwardly]
Can't think of anyone.

04:36.485 --> 04:38.236
-[door slams]
-[shudders]

04:38.236 --> 04:40.030
[♪ upbeat Indian
music playing]

04:45.035 --> 04:47.454
Ah! There's Prem, amazing!

04:47.454 --> 04:49.706
♪<i> My friends,
seeing you's the best</i> ♪

04:49.706 --> 04:52.209
♪<i> Your friendship
is the honey to my breakfast</i> ♪

04:52.209 --> 04:54.211
<i> ♪ Princess Nora,
merci, merci ♪</i>

04:54.211 --> 04:56.838
♪<i> Chouquettes and green tea
is a breakfast for free</i> ♪

04:56.838 --> 04:58.548
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

04:59.299 --> 05:00.634
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

05:00.634 --> 05:03.011
<i> ♪ Ah, bises a toi ♪</i>

05:03.887 --> 05:06.139
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

05:06.139 --> 05:07.891
<i> ♪ Prince Marc, merci, merci ♪</i>

05:07.891 --> 05:10.310
♪<i> For lending me the book
that had me totally shook</i> ♪

05:10.310 --> 05:12.771
<i> ♪ Prince Adrinette,
merci, merci ♪</i>

05:12.771 --> 05:15.148
♪<i> It took time to blossom,
now your love is awesome</i> ♪

05:15.148 --> 05:16.816
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

05:17.859 --> 05:19.110
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

05:19.110 --> 05:21.488
<i> ♪ Ah, bises a toi ♪</i>

05:22.280 --> 05:24.491
<i> ♪ Bises a toi ♪</i>

05:24.491 --> 05:26.701
<i> ♪ Princess Rose,
merci, merci ♪</i>

05:26.701 --> 05:28.912
♪<i> You and I
truly share the same energy</i> ♪

05:28.912 --> 05:31.498
♪<i> Have a nice day,
friends and crew</i> ♪

05:31.498 --> 05:34.000
♪<i> And again, thank you,
thank you</i> ♪

05:36.336 --> 05:38.255
What's the good news today,
friends?

05:38.255 --> 05:39.631
Marinette and Adrien
got tickets

05:39.631 --> 05:41.341
for the<i> Vampire Horrific
Musical Show.</i>

05:41.341 --> 05:43.969
How lucky!
I so wish I could have gone!

05:43.969 --> 05:46.680
Me too, it's my absolute
favorite movie.

05:46.680 --> 05:49.307
Those are lovely fangs
you got.

05:49.307 --> 05:51.017
Bite me tender!

05:51.017 --> 05:52.352
[scoffs and grumbles]

05:52.352 --> 05:54.062
Let me show you something.

05:54.771 --> 05:55.730
Oh...

05:57.148 --> 05:58.358
[grunts softly]

05:59.067 --> 06:01.861
[grunts, chuckles]

06:03.989 --> 06:07.409
Oh, just like in the<i> Vampire
Horrific Musical Show!</i>

06:07.409 --> 06:10.161
A vampire origami
for you, Princess Rose.

06:10.161 --> 06:13.540
[laughs] He gives presents
to Rose because he loves her!

06:13.540 --> 06:16.543
Yes, I love Princess Rose.
I love her as a friend,

06:16.543 --> 06:19.045
a sweet, kind friend.
[exclaims]

06:19.045 --> 06:21.381
[grunts] That's not
what we're seeing.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.592
Then what are you seeing?

06:23.592 --> 06:26.177
That she seems to be
more than just a sweet,
kind friend.

06:26.177 --> 06:29.055
-Leave Prem alone!
-[both grunt]

06:29.055 --> 06:31.141
Stop it!

06:31.141 --> 06:32.809
Feeling like a rebel, are we?

06:32.809 --> 06:34.644
Cockroach.

06:36.354 --> 06:37.647
-[grunts]
-Ah!

06:41.067 --> 06:43.486
You three are truly heartless.

06:43.486 --> 06:44.821
It's okay, Princess Marinette.

06:44.821 --> 06:46.906
They can destroy
all the origami
in the world,

06:46.906 --> 06:49.326
but they'll never destroy
how I feel about Princess Rose

06:49.326 --> 06:53.121
or the people closest to me.
Love always mends the heart.

06:53.121 --> 06:55.540
[Mylene] We're nice,
but we're not as nice as Prem.

06:55.540 --> 06:57.876
[laughs] And what are you
gonna do?

06:57.876 --> 07:00.920
We're gonna stop you
from bullying other people.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.672
You should be ashamed
of yourselves!

07:02.672 --> 07:04.466
[laughs] Pathetic!

07:04.466 --> 07:06.885
Absolutely pathetic!

07:07.969 --> 07:10.013
No, no, hold on, Ray.
They're right.

07:10.013 --> 07:12.182
Let's admit that maybe
we've gone too far

07:12.182 --> 07:13.433
and messed up school unity.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.185
Are you making fun of us,
Nelson?

07:15.185 --> 07:18.188
Of course not,
I really mean it.
What do you say?

07:18.188 --> 07:19.773
First, you should apologize.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.483
And repay Prem
for what you've done.

07:21.483 --> 07:23.026
Have you gone
completely bananas?

07:23.026 --> 07:24.903
You wanna give a gift
to that loser, Prem?

07:24.903 --> 07:27.822
More than that, Loic. I mean,
one gift would be generous,

07:27.822 --> 07:30.367
but two gifts
could turn poisonous.

07:30.367 --> 07:32.786
-Hmm?
-What are you talking about?

07:32.786 --> 07:35.288
Ray, you can get a hold
of anything you want, right?

07:35.288 --> 07:36.706
Obviously.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.250
Perfect.

07:39.250 --> 07:42.587
Two tickets for the<i> Vampire
Horrific Musical Show.</i>

07:43.588 --> 07:46.091
And now, watch and learn.

07:46.091 --> 07:49.803
[Prem] Whoa! But how...
how did you do it?
They were all sold out.

07:49.803 --> 07:51.513
There's always a spot
for someone

07:51.513 --> 07:53.556
who wants to redeem
themselves, isn't there?

07:53.556 --> 07:55.058
Prince Nelson,
thank you, thank you!

07:55.058 --> 07:56.810
I'm thrilled that
you've opened your heart

07:56.810 --> 07:58.895
to love like a sunflower
in the morning sun.

07:58.895 --> 08:00.689
I'll sing your praises
to everyone.

08:00.689 --> 08:02.649
Oh, that's not why I did it.

08:02.649 --> 08:04.484
A good deed
is a reward in itself.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.027
Let's keep this between us.

08:06.027 --> 08:08.947
You really are so generous
and so humble.

08:08.947 --> 08:11.408
Enjoy the movie with a friend.
What am I saying?

08:11.408 --> 08:13.827
With the princess
of your choosing.

08:15.036 --> 08:16.871
Whoo-hoo! [laughs]

08:25.755 --> 08:27.340
-Princess Rose! Princess Rose!
-Hmm?

08:27.340 --> 08:28.675
Look what I just got!

08:28.675 --> 08:31.803
Two tickets
for the<i> Vampire Horrific
Musical Show?</i>

08:31.803 --> 08:33.221
Who gave you those, Prem?

08:33.221 --> 08:34.514
Love has, Marinette!

08:34.514 --> 08:36.808
I told you,
love mends the heart.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.185
Will you go to the movies
with me, Princess Rose?

08:39.185 --> 08:40.228
Oh, yes!

08:40.228 --> 08:42.731
This is amazing,
now we can all go together.

08:42.731 --> 08:44.232
[laughs nervously]

08:45.150 --> 08:47.569
[Juleka sighs, groans]

08:47.569 --> 08:49.195
[Rose]<i> As he steps out
of the forest...</i>

08:49.195 --> 08:51.865
[Prem]<i> The vampire
places his hands
on Jenny's shoulders!</i>

08:51.865 --> 08:53.283
-Aah!
-And everyone in the theater

08:53.283 --> 08:55.660
must grab the shoulders of
the person in front of them.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.704
-That's so thrilling!
-[Adrien] Sounds like fun.

08:57.704 --> 08:58.997
Right. Fun.
[chuckles nervously]

08:58.997 --> 09:01.499
That's the exact word
I was about to use.

09:01.499 --> 09:03.626
-[chuckles nervously]
-Wait. Juleka!

09:03.626 --> 09:05.378
What are we gonna do
without Juleka?

09:05.378 --> 09:07.130
There are only two tickets.

09:07.130 --> 09:08.548
[Nelson] Show time!

09:08.548 --> 09:10.133
Oh... right!

09:10.133 --> 09:13.595
Princess Rose, you can't go
without your princess.

09:13.595 --> 09:15.555
Here, Princess Juleka,
have my ticket.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.682
No, no, you two go together.

09:18.725 --> 09:20.477
You look sad, Jule.

09:20.477 --> 09:21.561
No, I'm not.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.813
As long as you're happy,
so am I.

09:23.813 --> 09:27.317
You're gonna need make-up.
I can do it if you want.

09:27.317 --> 09:28.735
[Nelson] The seed of jealousy

09:28.735 --> 09:30.570
has been sewn
in the soil of love.

09:30.570 --> 09:31.905
[Loic] I didn't get
any of that.

09:31.905 --> 09:33.323
Your sentences are too wordy.

09:33.323 --> 09:35.241
[Ray] He said they're about
to break up, duh.

09:35.241 --> 09:38.745
[Marinette] It's not really
a horror movie since
it's also a musical,

09:38.745 --> 09:41.080
and everyone knows
that music soothes the soul.

09:41.080 --> 09:44.250
-I'm sure
it can't be that scary.
-[both] Whoa! Amazing!

09:44.250 --> 09:46.461
-[Marinette] Are you sure?
-Princess Marinette!

09:46.461 --> 09:48.963
You look
horrifyingly beautiful!

09:48.963 --> 09:50.048
My turn.

09:52.926 --> 09:54.302
Adrien, are you done?

09:54.302 --> 09:55.637
I'd like to use the mirror.

09:55.637 --> 09:57.806
[in Dracula accent]
I am ready!

09:57.806 --> 09:59.724
[Marinette screaming]

10:00.308 --> 10:01.309
[screaming]

10:01.309 --> 10:03.144
-What's up, kids?
-[growls]

10:03.144 --> 10:04.687
[Marinette screaming]

10:05.271 --> 10:06.731
Marinette, are you okay?

10:07.315 --> 10:08.733
[heavy breathing]

10:09.567 --> 10:10.652
[gasps]

10:10.652 --> 10:12.195
[screaming]

10:13.238 --> 10:15.490
Marinette, are you sure
you wanna go?

10:15.490 --> 10:17.659
Uh, of course!
I love being scared,

10:17.659 --> 10:19.244
screaming, yelling,
running away,

10:19.244 --> 10:21.955
and seeing your faces
with horrifying make-up!

10:21.955 --> 10:23.832
[Johnny] Now, let's go, kids.

10:23.832 --> 10:26.334
Or we'll miss
the start of the movie!

10:30.630 --> 10:32.632
-Have fun.
-Thanks, Jule!

10:32.632 --> 10:34.342
I'll call you
as soon as we're done

10:34.342 --> 10:35.802
and tell you all about it.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.762
Great. I can't wait.

10:38.304 --> 10:40.306
[Rose giggling]

10:47.313 --> 10:49.816
You can't let Rose
and Prem be alone together.

10:49.816 --> 10:52.318
Come on, get up!
We're going to the movies

10:52.318 --> 10:55.989
so you can tell them how you
really feel. Be a fighter!

10:58.950 --> 10:59.993
[beeps]

11:00.827 --> 11:02.161
<i> Hey, Juleka.</i>

11:04.455 --> 11:05.540
<i> What's wrong, sis?</i>

11:05.540 --> 11:07.375
Why aren't you here anymore?

11:07.375 --> 11:08.835
<i> Of course I'm here. See?</i>

11:08.835 --> 11:11.838
No, you're no longer here
beside me.

11:11.838 --> 11:13.548
Now that there's an ocean
between us,

11:13.548 --> 11:14.883
nothing's the same anymore.

11:14.883 --> 11:17.010
We used to be
able to tell each
other everything

11:17.010 --> 11:18.761
all the time.
Now I'm all alone.

11:18.761 --> 11:20.471
<i> You have Rose.</i>

11:21.055 --> 11:23.683
What if she left me someday
like you did?

11:23.683 --> 11:25.351
What if she found
someone better than me?

11:25.351 --> 11:28.688
Someone who's like her,
someone she can share
everything with.

11:28.688 --> 11:31.816
<i> Stop it, Jule. I'm sure you're
getting worried over nothing.</i>

11:32.859 --> 11:34.485
You don't know that.
You're not here.

11:34.485 --> 11:37.530
There's only one person
I can count on anyway, myself.

11:37.530 --> 11:38.948
-<i> Jul--
</i>-[beeps]

11:41.784 --> 11:43.453
[grunting]

11:44.621 --> 11:46.039
[breathing heavily]

11:46.039 --> 11:48.958
Yeah, things are always better
with action!

11:48.958 --> 11:51.878
[♪ sinister music playing]

11:51.878 --> 11:53.546
[Marinette whimpering]

11:53.546 --> 11:56.174
[Marinette] No need
to grab my shoulders
during the movie, okay?

11:56.174 --> 11:58.343
It's not gonna scare me.
[chuckles nervously]

12:03.348 --> 12:06.559
If you fold it
along the dotted line,
you get a paper bat.

12:06.559 --> 12:09.520
Then you can throw it
at the right time
during the movie.

12:09.520 --> 12:10.897
-[man laughing]
-[Marinette gasps]

12:10.897 --> 12:12.899
[man cackling]

12:12.899 --> 12:14.400
[whimpers] Aah!

12:15.944 --> 12:17.070
-[phone rings]
-Aah!

12:17.070 --> 12:19.322
Shoot! Sorry.
I forgot to turn it off.

12:21.240 --> 12:23.159
Hmm? Luka?

12:23.159 --> 12:25.078
<i> Did something happen
between you and Juleka?</i>

12:25.078 --> 12:27.246
Uh, no. Things are good, why?

12:35.755 --> 12:37.757
[Bourgeois]
Horrific evening, everyone!

12:37.757 --> 12:39.384
And welcome
to the special screening

12:39.384 --> 12:42.553
of the<i> Vampire Horrific
Musical Show!</i>

12:42.553 --> 12:45.014
For the first time in France,
you're about to watch

12:45.014 --> 12:47.684
an extended,
unreleased version
with exclusive

12:47.684 --> 12:49.519
and even more
terrifying footage!

12:49.519 --> 12:53.439
Thirty additional minutes
of thrill, anguish, horror,

12:53.439 --> 12:55.274
terror, fear, fright!

12:55.274 --> 12:57.318
[Marinette] I'd have been
fine with anguish.

12:57.318 --> 12:59.153
We can leave
if you want to, Marinette.

12:59.153 --> 13:02.156
Oh, no, nonsense.
I love it when my heart
jumps out of my chest.

13:02.156 --> 13:04.117
Horror movies are the best.

13:04.117 --> 13:06.703
-[Rose grunting]
-Where are you going,
Princess Rose?

13:06.703 --> 13:09.288
Juleka's not okay
and it's my fault.

13:09.288 --> 13:12.166
She's always there for me and
tonight I'm not there for her.

13:12.166 --> 13:13.710
I didn't realize
she'd be so sad

13:13.710 --> 13:15.712
if I went to this movie
without her.

13:15.712 --> 13:17.839
[music stops]

13:17.839 --> 13:19.632
-I'll go with Rose.
-No, you stay. I'll go.

13:19.632 --> 13:22.218
No, no, no. This is
an important moment for you
and your grandparents.

13:22.218 --> 13:25.013
-You're gonna miss the movie.
-It's okay, I already
hate it anyway.

13:25.013 --> 13:27.682
-But--
-Adrien, you were
right all along,

13:27.682 --> 13:29.308
I still don't like
horror movies,

13:29.308 --> 13:30.977
but I was afraid
not coming with you

13:30.977 --> 13:32.520
would drive us away
from each other,

13:32.520 --> 13:35.314
that you'd be
disappointed in me,
that you'd love me less.

13:35.314 --> 13:37.483
Marinette, the only thing
that could disappoint me

13:37.483 --> 13:39.360
is if you feel
you can't be honest with me

13:39.360 --> 13:42.321
and you force yourself
to do something you don't
want to just to please me.

13:44.198 --> 13:45.491
[kisses]

13:45.491 --> 13:47.160
Ugh, the blame falls upon me.

13:47.160 --> 13:50.079
I'm the one
who caused such distress
between Rose and Juleka.

13:50.079 --> 13:51.998
I did something horrific.

13:51.998 --> 13:54.542
I'm horrific! I'm horrific!

14:02.216 --> 14:03.342
Huh?

14:04.886 --> 14:07.305
[Chrysalis]
Hello, forgive my intrusion,

14:07.305 --> 14:09.515
but I sensed a great deal
of guilt.

14:09.515 --> 14:11.225
Get out of my head,
evil super villain!

14:11.225 --> 14:13.061
I've done enough harm
as it is today.

14:13.061 --> 14:15.438
If I listen to you, I'll make
someone else broken hearted.

14:15.438 --> 14:17.732
You're wrong about
my intensions, dear Prem.

14:17.732 --> 14:20.902
People think
I'm an evil person
like the former Hawk Moth,

14:20.902 --> 14:24.155
when really I only want
to help my fellow humans.

14:24.155 --> 14:25.656
Why should I believe you?

14:25.656 --> 14:27.408
Because I'm offering you
the power

14:27.408 --> 14:29.494
of your choosing
and I'm not asking

14:29.494 --> 14:31.788
for anything in return.

14:31.788 --> 14:34.791
Not even Ladybug
and Cat Noir's Miraculous.

14:34.791 --> 14:38.252
<i> What more
do you need to believe
I'm acting selflessly?</i>

14:38.252 --> 14:40.630
<i> -[Prem] You're
not tricking me?
-Of course not.</i>

14:40.630 --> 14:43.674
Just tell me
what I should call you
and see for yourself.

14:43.674 --> 14:45.176
Fine...

14:45.176 --> 14:47.261
then call me Count Vampigami!

14:48.638 --> 14:50.139
[whirring]

14:53.059 --> 14:55.645
[♪ sultry rock music playing]

14:57.396 --> 14:59.315
Huh? Aah!

14:59.315 --> 15:02.068
If princesses Rose and Juleka
can't come to the movie,

15:02.068 --> 15:04.779
the movie will come
to the princesses!

15:04.779 --> 15:06.864
[Rose muffled screaming]

15:06.864 --> 15:10.118
-[crowd screams]
-[woman] Move! I think
we should get out of here!

15:10.118 --> 15:12.370
[crowd clamoring]

15:12.370 --> 15:16.040
I'm not Prem.
I'm Count Vampigami.

15:16.833 --> 15:18.042
[grunts]

15:18.042 --> 15:19.669
-[claps]
-[beeping]

15:19.669 --> 15:21.170
[Adrien gasps, grunts]

15:21.170 --> 15:22.797
-[chimes]
-[Adrien whimpers]

15:22.797 --> 15:23.965
[Vampigami chuckles, claps]

15:23.965 --> 15:25.716
[chuckling]

15:25.716 --> 15:27.176
-Hah!
-[screaming]

15:27.176 --> 15:28.427
[Adrien shudders]

15:28.427 --> 15:30.638
-[whoosh]
-[woman] What's happening?

15:31.097 --> 15:32.640
[woman exclaiming
indistinctly]

15:34.892 --> 15:36.435
[water trickling]

15:38.980 --> 15:40.273
[gasps]

15:40.273 --> 15:42.358
[Tikki] Quiet, Marinette!
Don't say a word!

15:42.358 --> 15:44.277
And whatever you do,
do not transform.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.612
There's a video camera above.

15:46.612 --> 15:48.739
Unlike Kwamis,
you can be filmed
and recorded,

15:48.739 --> 15:51.284
so just act like you're afraid
of the akumatized villain

15:51.284 --> 15:53.286
and you've come here to hide.

15:56.747 --> 15:58.040
[door handle rattling]

15:58.583 --> 15:59.625
[Adrien grunting]

16:01.794 --> 16:03.546
[panting]

16:09.468 --> 16:10.803
Plagg, Claws Out!

16:10.803 --> 16:12.096
[zaps]

16:13.723 --> 16:15.433
Cataclysm!

16:15.850 --> 16:18.311
-[grunts]
-[crowd shouting]

16:19.145 --> 16:21.480
Princess Rose, stay, stay!

16:21.480 --> 16:24.400
Vampigami and his friends
will go get Juleka for you.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.611
If leaving that girl alone
is beyond your skills,

16:26.611 --> 16:29.071
then you're the worst vampire
friend there is.

16:29.071 --> 16:32.033
I'm not in the mood for jokes,
fuzz bucket!

16:32.033 --> 16:35.077
Step aside or get ready
to express regret!

16:40.166 --> 16:43.085
[Cat Noir] Okay! So, I guess
we won't be premiering

16:43.085 --> 16:45.338
our duet in concert. Too bad!

16:50.760 --> 16:52.720
Cataclysm! Cataclysm!

16:52.720 --> 16:54.347
Cataclysm! Whoa...

16:55.181 --> 16:57.350
Cataclysm! [grunts]

16:57.350 --> 16:58.893
[panting]

16:58.893 --> 17:00.436
A super ladybug
would give me wings

17:00.436 --> 17:02.605
provided that her phone rings.

17:04.148 --> 17:06.150
[Marinette panting]

17:09.987 --> 17:11.155
[grunts]

17:11.572 --> 17:12.782
[whimpers]

17:12.782 --> 17:15.076
Locked doors at the theater,
a camera in the bathroom,

17:15.076 --> 17:17.662
it's like someone knew
there'd be an akumatization
there today.

17:17.662 --> 17:19.330
It could be a trap
from the new holder

17:19.330 --> 17:20.790
of the Butterfly Miraculous.

17:20.790 --> 17:23.292
I don't know,
but we're gonna have
to be extra careful.

17:23.292 --> 17:25.628
-Tikki, Spots On!
-[zaps]

17:26.545 --> 17:27.713
Hmm?

17:27.713 --> 17:29.215
[beeping]

17:29.215 --> 17:31.175
Got your message.
On my way, Kitty Kat.

17:31.175 --> 17:33.719
-[whirring]
-[trilling]

17:36.138 --> 17:38.182
[Vampigami] Why prevent love
from prevailing?

17:38.182 --> 17:40.059
Join the ranks, Cat Noir,

17:40.059 --> 17:42.228
or the ranks will join you.

17:42.228 --> 17:44.063
[♪ dramatic music playing]

17:47.066 --> 17:48.567
For now,
I'll be the one joining him!

17:48.567 --> 17:50.236
Keep away from the kitty,
vampires.

17:50.236 --> 17:52.238
Ah, my lady!
So glad to see you!

17:52.238 --> 17:54.240
[giggles]
Yeah, same, I'm super glad.

17:54.240 --> 17:57.034
I love scary vampires.
[chuckles nervously]

17:57.034 --> 17:58.244
[grunts]

17:58.744 --> 18:00.329
[both grunting]

18:01.455 --> 18:03.582
-[Ladybug yells]
-[Cat Noir grunts]

18:03.582 --> 18:06.043
And these ones sing too.
Vampigami over there,

18:06.043 --> 18:07.586
he's the one running the show.

18:07.586 --> 18:10.589
[Ladybug] He doesn't
look terrifying at all!
[nervous laughter]

18:10.589 --> 18:12.675
-[teeth chattering]
-Is that noise
coming from you?

18:12.675 --> 18:15.344
Me? No! What noise?
Oh, right! It's my fingers.

18:15.344 --> 18:16.762
I can't help it.
Whenever I hear music,

18:16.762 --> 18:18.764
I have to snap my fingers.
[chuckles nervously]

18:18.764 --> 18:20.182
[♪ music continues]

18:20.182 --> 18:22.226
[beeping]

18:24.729 --> 18:26.105
[whooshes]

18:28.566 --> 18:31.068
This music does make you want
to sing and clap your hands.

18:31.068 --> 18:33.988
Vampigami, on the other hand,
must be stopped
from clapping his hands.

18:33.988 --> 18:35.531
Well spotted, M'Lady.

18:35.531 --> 18:38.617
When he claps his hands,
his zombie dancers
get new battle origamis.

18:38.617 --> 18:40.619
-Hi, friends.
-Pigella, Purple Tigress,

18:40.619 --> 18:43.873
you're right on time
for the vampire dance.

18:43.873 --> 18:46.292
Cat Noir, get the party
started with your cataclysms.

18:46.292 --> 18:48.461
I've got you covered.
Lucky Charm!

18:49.420 --> 18:50.379
[grunts]

18:53.758 --> 18:55.384
Cataclysm!

18:55.384 --> 18:58.054
Superheroes always make
the best games,

18:58.054 --> 19:01.182
so you zombies
can put away your... fangs!

19:01.182 --> 19:02.308
[Cat Noir grunting]

19:02.308 --> 19:04.518
-Purple Tigress, you're up.
-Gladly.

19:04.977 --> 19:06.937
Clout! Aah!

19:06.937 --> 19:08.439
Huh?

19:08.439 --> 19:11.275
[groaning, screaming]

19:12.443 --> 19:14.028
[Ladybug]
Pigella, you're next!

19:14.028 --> 19:15.363
[whimpering]

19:15.363 --> 19:16.572
-Gift!
-[chimes]

19:16.572 --> 19:18.324
-[Vampigami yells]
-[thuds]

19:18.324 --> 19:20.576
[groans] Hmm?

19:20.576 --> 19:21.535
[shudders]

19:26.499 --> 19:27.833
[gasping]

19:28.542 --> 19:29.627
[grunts]

19:31.670 --> 19:33.214
[glass breaking]

19:34.590 --> 19:37.426
[Ladybug] No more evil-doing
for you, Ultrakuma.

19:41.305 --> 19:43.307
Time to de-evilize!

19:46.977 --> 19:48.437
Gotcha!

19:49.313 --> 19:50.898
Bye-bye, little butterfly.

19:52.024 --> 19:54.860
-Miraculous Ladybug!
-[chimes]

19:58.030 --> 19:59.281
[crowd shudders]

20:01.992 --> 20:03.160
[Prem] Hmm?

20:03.160 --> 20:04.870
Ladybug, what did I do?

20:04.870 --> 20:06.330
[whirring]

20:07.998 --> 20:09.291
[chimes]

20:10.418 --> 20:12.711
[Ladybug] This magical charm
will help you remember

20:12.711 --> 20:15.381
that you can dance on your own
or with another person,

20:15.381 --> 20:17.425
or even in a group,
but that some people

20:17.425 --> 20:20.636
may just not want to dance
and that's okay too.

20:20.636 --> 20:21.720
[all] Pound it!

20:22.596 --> 20:23.597
[both grunt]

20:23.597 --> 20:24.890
Hmm?

20:27.226 --> 20:29.061
Cat Noir, the new holder
of the Miraculous

20:29.061 --> 20:32.189
is not trying to defeat us
by using their akumatized
villains to fight us.

20:32.189 --> 20:35.401
They want to defeat us
by figuring out
who we really are.

20:35.401 --> 20:37.736
They're spying on us.
I already had a feeling

20:37.736 --> 20:40.364
but it was confirmed today.
We've got to stay alert.

20:41.031 --> 20:43.200
You can count on me.

20:43.200 --> 20:45.035
[Prem] I'm sorry,
Princess Juleka.

20:45.035 --> 20:47.580
I never wanted to form
rain clouds in the blue sky

20:47.580 --> 20:49.331
of your relationship
with Princess Rose

20:49.331 --> 20:51.333
or upset you. If this
is gonna bring you sadness,

20:51.333 --> 20:54.753
I'd rather not see the movie
with Princess Rose.
You go with her.

20:56.755 --> 20:59.633
I'm not upset with you, Prem.
I'm upset with myself

20:59.633 --> 21:02.178
'cause I felt like, since you
and Rose liked the same movie,

21:02.178 --> 21:04.638
you were meant for each other
more than Rose and me.

21:04.638 --> 21:08.267
No way, Jule.
It's nothing like that.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.644
I'm so scared of losing you,

21:10.644 --> 21:13.314
but I'm gonna try
to overcome that fear.

21:13.314 --> 21:15.483
Just because we don't do
everything together

21:15.483 --> 21:17.943
doesn't mean that we don't
love each other very much,

21:17.943 --> 21:21.280
and there's no one I love
more than you, Jule.

21:23.199 --> 21:25.451
Go see the movie together.
I'll be fine.

21:25.451 --> 21:28.412
Or you go. You can have
my ticket if you want.

21:28.412 --> 21:30.789
Have mine,
I hate horror movies anyway.

21:30.789 --> 21:32.124
[Rose] Are you sure?

21:32.124 --> 21:35.336
Rose is right,
just because you don't do
everything together

21:35.336 --> 21:37.296
doesn't mean
that you love each other less.

21:37.296 --> 21:39.298
[Johnny] Hey, kids!
Time to go.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.759
Or we'll miss the start
of the movie!

21:43.511 --> 21:44.803
[both] I love you.

21:44.803 --> 21:46.180
[Loic] Gag me.

21:46.180 --> 21:49.391
[Nelson] More couples
just means more fun...
breaking them up.

21:49.391 --> 21:50.684
[boys chuckle]

21:56.524 --> 21:58.442
[shrieks, screams]

22:10.162 --> 22:12.831
[shrieks, screams]

22:16.835 --> 22:20.256
[Lila] It has to be her.
It's the only
logical explanation.

22:20.256 --> 22:22.800
<i> If it were her, she would have
transformed there and then,</i>

22:22.800 --> 22:25.261
-<i> but she didn't.
</i>-[Lila] I'm missing something.

22:25.261 --> 22:27.388
It's not possible.
It has to be her.

22:27.388 --> 22:29.807
<i> You have to explore
other avenues, Lila.</i>

22:32.351 --> 22:34.395
[Lila] Tatsu, drive me home.

22:37.481 --> 22:40.359
[♪ theme music playing]
